    <item>
      <title>Advanced Features</title>
      <link>/stop3DS/discussions/advancedfeatures/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/stop3DS/discussions/advancedfeatures/</guid>
      <description>Overview There are many features I would consider &amp;ldquo;advanced&amp;rdquo; in that they go beyond a simple frame-by-frame drawing and animation app. These features include things such as &amp;ldquo;sprite&amp;rdquo; support, assets that can be manipulated and treated as objects (moved, transformed) without having to manually redraw everything. More interestingly this can lead to &amp;ldquo;smart animation&amp;rdquo; or sprites that react inputs from the user such as a fish reacting to food as seen in Bret Victor&amp;rsquo;s video &amp;ldquo;Stop drawing dead fish&amp;rdquo;.</description>
    </item>
    
